---
import Section from '../components/Section.astro';
import Math from '../components/Math.astro';
---

<Section id="abstract" title="Abstract">
  <p>
    We extend the Social Force Model of Helbing, Farkas and Vicsek (2000)
    with a per-agent stress level <Math tex={String.raw`\beta_i(t) \in [0, 1]`} /> that
    follows an SIR-style contagion ODE. Stress decays at rate
    <Math tex={String.raw`\mu`} /> and spreads between neighbours through a
    speed-dependent kernel of strength <Math tex={String.raw`\kappa`} /> and range
    <Math tex={String.raw`\ell`} />. Stress in turn raises each agent's desired walking
    speed through a linear link
    <Math tex={String.raw`v_0(\beta) = V_{\min} + (V_{\max} - V_{\min})\beta`} />,
    coupling psychological state to physical motion.
  </p>

  <p>
    A mean-field reduction of the contagion ODE produces a logistic
    equation governed by the reproduction number
    <Math tex={String.raw`R_0 = 2\pi\rho\kappa\ell^{2}/\mu`} />. The system undergoes
    a transcritical bifurcation at <Math tex={String.raw`R_0 = 1`} />: below the
    threshold panic dies out, above it the crowd settles into an endemic
    stress equilibrium <Math tex={String.raw`\beta^{*} = 1 - 1/R_0`} />. Agent-based
    simulations confirm the mean-field curve and reveal a U-shaped
    evacuation-time profile as a function of initial collective stress,
    with an optimum at <Math tex={String.raw`\Sigma_0^{*} \approx 0.47`} />.
  </p>

  <p>
    The two results combine into a closed-form critical crowd size
    <Math tex={String.raw`N^{*} = \mu A / (2\pi\kappa\ell^{2})`} /> above which
    sustained panic is unavoidable, and a monotonically decreasing
    optimal stress <Math tex={String.raw`\Sigma_0^{*}(N)`} />. Three modelling
    parameters map onto three measurable design levers: density
    <Math tex={String.raw`\rho`} /> (exit width), contagion strength
    <Math tex={String.raw`\kappa`} /> (authoritative information), and influence
    range <Math tex={String.raw`\ell`} /> (visual separators).
  </p>

  <p
    class="text-[0.92rem] mt-4"
    style="color: var(--color-muted); font-family: var(--font-sans);"
  >
    <strong style="color: var(--color-ink-soft);">Keywords:</strong>
    crowd dynamics, social force model, stress contagion, faster-is-slower,
    transcritical bifurcation, evacuation, agent-based modelling.
  </p>
</Section>
